Harecastle Tunnel.label: Harecastle Tunnel
Harecastle Tunnel.description: Harecastle Tunnel is a canal tunnel on the Trent and Mersey Canal at Kidsgrove in Staffordshire. It is made up of two separate, parallel, tunnels described as Brindley and the later Telford after the engineers that constructed them. Wikipedia

Islington Tunnel.label: Islington Tunnel
Islington Tunnel.description: The Islington Tunnel carries the Regent's Canal Arm of the Grand Union Canal for 960 yards underneath the Angel area of Islington, in London. The two other tunnels on the Regent's Canal are Eyre's tunnel and Maida Hill Tunnel. Wikipedia

Greywell Tunnel.label: Greywell Tunnel
Greywell Tunnel.description: The Greywell Tunnel is a 0.6 hectare biological Site of Special Scientific Interest in Hampshire, England, notified in 1985. When opened in 1794 it was the longest tunnel on the Basingstoke Canal. It was closed due to a roof fall in 1932. Wikipedia

Standedge Tunnels.label: Standedge Tunnels
Standedge Tunnels.description: The Standedge Tunnels are four parallel tunnels beneath the Pennines in northern England. Three are railway tunnels and the other a canal tunnel, located at the Standedge crossing point between Marsden ... Wikipedia

Blisworth Tunnel.label: Blisworth Tunnel
Blisworth Tunnel.description: Blisworth Tunnel is a canal tunnel on the Grand Union Canal in Northamptonshire, England between the villages of Stoke Bruerne at the southern end and Blisworth at the northern end. Wikipedia

Bruce Tunnel.label: Bruce Tunnel
Bruce Tunnel.description:
The Bruce Tunnel is on the summit pound of the Kennet and Avon Canal between Wootton Top Lock and Crofton Locks in Wiltshire, England.
This is the only tunnel on the canal and it is 502 yards long. Wikipedia

Netherton Tunnel Branch Canal.label: Netherton Tunnel Branch Canal
Netherton Tunnel Branch Canal.description: Netherton Tunnel Branch Canal, in the English West Midlands, is part of the Birmingham Canal Navigations,. It was constructed at a 453–foot elevation, the Wednesbury or Birmingham level; it has no locks. Wikipedia

Chirk Tunnel.label: Chirk Tunnel
Chirk Tunnel.description:
Chirk Tunnel is a canal tunnel near Chirk, Wales.
It lies on the Llangollen Canal, immediately northwards of the Chirk Aqueduct. It is 421 metres long and has a complete towpath inside. Wikipedia

Norwood Tunnel.label: Norwood Tunnel
Norwood Tunnel.description: Norwood Tunnel was a 2,884-yard-long, 9.25-foot-wide and 12-foot-high brick lined canal tunnel on the line of the Chesterfield Canal with its Western Portal in Norwood, Derbyshire and its Eastern Portal in Kiveton, South Yorkshire, England. Wikipedia

Shrewley Tunnel.label: Shrewley Tunnel
Shrewley Tunnel.description: Shrewley Tunnel is a canal tunnel near Shrewley, Warwickshire, England, which opened in 1799. It became part of the Grand Union Canal in 1929. Wikipedia

Maida Hill Tunnel.label: Maida Hill Tunnel
Maida Hill Tunnel.description: Maida Hill Tunnel is a canal tunnel on the Regent's Canal in London. The two other tunnels on the Regent's Canal are Islington Tunnel and Eyre's tunnel. Wikipedia

Braunston Tunnel.label: Braunston Tunnel
Braunston Tunnel.description:
Braunston Tunnel is situated on the Grand Union Canal about 830 yds east of Braunston, Northamptonshire, England top lock.
Braunston Tunnel is 2,042 yards in length. Wikipedia

Sapperton Canal Tunnel.label: Sapperton Canal Tunnel
Sapperton Canal Tunnel.description: The Sapperton Canal Tunnel is a tunnel on the Thames and Severn Canal near Cirencester in Gloucestershire, England. With a length of 3,817 yards it was the longest canal tunnel, and the longest tunnel of any kind, in England from 1789 to 1811. Wikipedia

Berwick Tunnel.label: Berwick Tunnel
Berwick Tunnel.description: Berwick Tunnel is a canal tunnel located on the Shrewsbury Canal, Shropshire, England, UK. Wikipedia

Butterley Tunnel.label: Butterley Tunnel
Butterley Tunnel.description: Butterley Tunnel is a one and three quarter mile long canal tunnel on the Cromford Canal below Ripley, in Derbyshire, England, opened to traffic in 1794. Wikipedia

Lapal Tunnel.label: Lapal Tunnel
Lapal Tunnel.description: The Lapal Tunnel is a disused 3,470-metre canal tunnel on the five mile dry section of the Dudley No. 2 Canal in the West Midlands, England. It takes its name from the settlement of Lapal. Wikipedia

Bosporus Water Tunnel.label: Bosporus Water Tunnel
Bosporus Water Tunnel.description: The Bosphorus Water Tunnel is an under sea waterway tunnel in Istanbul, Turkey, crossing the Bosphorus strait. It was constructed in 2012 to transfer water from the Melen Creek in Düzce Province to the European side of Istanbul. Wikipedia
